Thirdly, All carnal and secure Worldlings▪ who although they do enquire where they may buy a good bargain, or get a good purchase, and labour for that, yet never enquire, Where Christ feeds his Sheep. Oh! it is a wonder to see how men covet pleasures, profits and preferments; these they seek with might and main; surely by this they declare to the World, that they are none of Christ's Sheep 
                     •
                   for if they were, they would hear his voice, and follow him, Joh. 10.27,
